{"id":897,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":897,"title":"Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar","subtitle":"","short_title":"Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar","uri":"/scriptures/bd/nebuchadnezzar","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/nebuchadnezzar.t1","order":".000.2358"},[".title","Nebuchadnezzar, Nebuchadrezzar"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/nebuchadnezzar.p1","order":".000.2359"},"Or Nabu-kudur-usur.",["i","Nebo, protect the crown!"],"(or,",["i","the landmark"],"). The great king of Babylon (604–561",["span.small","B.C."],"), son of Nabopolassar, the founder of the empire (see",["i",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/assyria-and-babylonia"},"Assyria and Babylonia"]],"); defeats Necho, king of Egypt, at Carchemish and drives the Egyptians from Syria (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/46.2-12"},"Jer. 46:2–12"],"); subdues Judah (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.1"},"2 Kgs. 24:1"],"); besieges Jerusalem (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/24.10-11"},"24:10–11"],") and takes it, carrying away the king and people (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/25.1,8,22"},"25:1, 8, 22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/6.15"},"1 Chr. 6:15"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/36"},"2 Chr. 36"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/1.7"},"Ezra 1:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/2.1"},"2:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/5.12,14"},"5:12, 14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ezra/6.5"},"6:5"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/neh/7.6"},"Neh. 7:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/esth/2.6"},"Esth. 2:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/27.6,8,20"},"Jer. 27:6, 8, 20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/28.3,11,14"},"28:3, 11, 14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/29.1,3"},"29:1, 3"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/34.1"},"34:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/jer/39.5"},"39:5"],"). For his relations with Daniel, by whom his dreams were interpreted, see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/dan/1?span=1-5"},"Dan. 1–5"],". He was for a time smitten with madness and on his recovery acknowledged God’s power and goodness."]]],"refs":null}
